Question: Why is the woman meeting with the man?
Description:
w4: Hi, Mr. Polk. Thanks for meeting with me.
M3: Sure. It's a pleasure. So, you're writing an article for Forge Ahead Magazine?
w4: Yes, the piece is about how your car
manufacturing plant dramatically changed the way it produces cars. Could you tell me about what you did?
M3: Certainly. Many factory employees are told to never stop the production line-no matter what.
Recently I took the opposite approach. Whenever we found a defect, anyone could stop the assembly line and address the problem immediately.
w4: And this transition improved your quality control?
M3: Exactly. In fact, look at this production chart. You'll see that, compared to other factories, cars from this one have far fewer defects.
